Sentencas: The long term performance of SOFC with nanocomposite Ni-YSZ anode and LSM-YSZ cathode was reported.
Titulo: Stability and Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Nanocomposite Electrodes

Sentencas: The SOFC was prepared by infiltrating polymeric precursors of NiO and LSM from anode and cathode sides respectively.
Titulo: Stability and Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Nanocomposite Electrodes

Sentencas: The fuel cell showed relatively high initial performance (0.49 Watt/cm(2) at 800 degrees C) for the given electrolyte thickness (similar to 170 mu m).
Titulo: Stability and Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Nanocomposite Electrodes

Sentencas: Long term stability tests showed that the power density dropped to 0.41 Watt/cm(2) in the first 60 hours of operation in short circuit conditions and no further change in the power density was observed.
Titulo: Stability and Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Nanocomposite Electrodes

Sentencas: Low electrode polarization resistance was obtained (similar to 0.080 Ohm.cm(2) for combined anode and cathode at 800 degrees C) which showed no significant change with prolonged time.
Titulo: Stability and Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Nanocomposite Electrodes

Sentencas: The slight drop in power density was related to the change in ohmic resistance which was attributed to the increase in current collection resistance.
Titulo: Stability and Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Nanocomposite Electrodes

Sentencas: The fact that the majority of the resistance was due to the electrolyte resistance (similar to 80%) suggests that stable SOFCs with high power densities could be achieved with thinner electrolytes.
Titulo: Stability and Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Nanocomposite Electrodes

Sentencas: After > 100 hours of operation at 800 degrees C in short circuit conditions, the fuel cell was measured at higher temperatures.
Titulo: Stability and Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Nanocomposite Electrodes

Sentencas: Power densities were 0.71 Watt/cm(2) and 1.0 Watt/cm(2) at 900 degrees C and 1000 degrees C, respectively.
